-- Markit IPO may value company at about $4.47 bln
-- 
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 06:13PM EDT
-- None



June 3 (Reuters) - Financial information service provider Markit Ltd [IPO-MRKT.O] said it expected its IPO to be priced at $23-$25 per share, which could value the company at up to $4.47 billion.

The company, which competes with Bloomberg and Thomson Reuters Corp <TRI.TO>, said selling shareholders, including certain employees and members of the management, were offering 45.7 million common shares. (http://link.reuters.com/zaz79v) The IPO could raise as much as $1.14 billion. The company intends to list its common stock on the Nasdaq under the symbol "MRKT".